===Etymology===
Old English [[segne]] < West Germanic *'''sagina''' < Latin [[sagena]] < Greek [[σαγήνη]] ("dragnet"), of unknown origin.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
#{{cattag|fishing}} A long [[net]] having [[float]]s attached at the top and [[sinker]]s (weights) at the bottom, used in shallow water for catching fish.

